CORNELIUS H. A. WILDMAN v. EDNA MAY WILDMAN. [No. 4,

October Term, 1931.]

Decided February 3rd, 1932.

The cause was argued before Bone, O. J., Urneb, Adkins, Oeeutt, Parke, and Sloan, JL.

Eugene Frederick, with whom were Blades, Rosenfeld & Frederick on the brief, for the appellant. Richard H. Stevenson, for the appellee. Sloan, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
